race.comment: KEEP IT REAL (4) two-start gelding who finished runner-up in both starts in his first campaign. Wasn't pushed out in his two jump outs and the cross-over nose band goes on. Capable of finishing over the top of these. GREAT FUEGO (7) heavily supported at her second run back when a game on-pace second over 1300m at Seymour. Poorly drawn but sure to be competitive in a fairly average race. ARU VALLEY (2) Astern gelding from a Lonhro mare on debut for the Feek yard. Has looked okay in all five jump outs and gets every chance from the good gate. Each-way player. TIJOLA (5) returns a gelding after chipping away on debut when fifth in the heavy going over 1000m at Bendigo last July. Fitted with the two searching jump outs and can overcome the sticky gate.
